|15,73
     An implied field use can only appear in a WITH block.  The WITH block
begins with a statement of the form

          with RECORD-NAME do begin ...

The RECORD-NAME is the name of a record variable.  Inside the WITH block,
you can refer to fields of that record just by "field" instead of
"recordname.field".
|mFor more, choose
|iDo nothing,nop
|iRecord Declarations,Hpnode/record_type
|iWith blocks,Hpnode/with_block
|iField use,Hpnode/field_use
|p
